CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1946, pg. 11 reads: "Pastor's Installation - Rev. S.L.Spear, pastor-elect of the Metropolitan Baptist Church as he was being presented to Rev. J.W. Parrish, who delivered the installation sermon and induction charge at the 11:00 A.M. services Sunday, Jan. 27. Metropolitan is Pittsburgh's oldest Baptist church. - Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, left to right: Rev. Samuel L. Spear, possibly Deacon Diggs, and Rev. J.W. Parrish, clasping hands and standing near lectern in Metropolitan Baptist Church
